We start by identifying the needed data from the provided statements.

Step 1. Operating Cash Flow Ratio 
• Formula: Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
• From the cash‐flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –224,133.22  
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable = 545,000.00 + 284,755.77 = 829,755.77  
• Calculation: –224,133.22 / 829,755.77 ≈ –0.27

Step 2. Cash Flow to Debt Ratio  
• Often defined in this context as: Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Debt  
• In the absence of separate long–term debt, we take Total Debt = Total Current Liabilities = 829,755.77  
• Calculation: –224,133.22 / 829,755.77 ≈ –0.27

Step 3. Inventory Turnover Ratio  
• Formula: Inventory Turnover Ratio = Cost of Goods Sold / Average Inventory  
• Cost of Goods Sold (COGS) from the income statement = 3,085,000.00  
• Inventories: Since the beginning inventory is 0.00 and the ending inventory is 720,000.00,  
  Average Inventory = (0.00 + 720,000.00) / 2 = 360,000.00  
• Calculation: 3,085,000.00 / 360,000.00 ≈ 8.57

Step 4. Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Formula: Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Debt / Total Owner's Equity  
• Total Debt (again, here using current liabilities) = 829,755.77  
• Total Owner’s Equity from balance sheet = 14,193,771.08  
• Calculation: 829,755.77 / 14,193,771.08 ≈ 0.06

Step 5. Quick Ratio  
• Formula: Quick Ratio = (Total Current Assets – Inventory) / Total Current Liabilities  
• Total Current Assets = 9,963,057.95 and Inventory = 720,000.00  
  Quick assets = 9,963,057.95 – 720,000.00 = 9,243,057.95  
• Calculation: 9,243,057.95 / 829,755.77 ≈ 11.14

Step 6. Current Ratio  
• Formula: Current Ratio = Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
• Calculation: 9,963,057.95 / 829,755.77 ≈ 12.01

Thus, the final answers are:

    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-0.27",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-0.27",
    "Inventory Turnover Ratio": "8.57",
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.06",
    "Quick Ratio": "11.14",
    "Current Ratio": "12.01"
  }
}
